<scopecontent>
<p>JOHN T. HARRIS PERSONAL AND FAMILY PAPERS, 1843-1936. This series encompassing John T. Harris's personal papers includes his law license, a will written in 1861, and his post-Civil War oath of allegiance to the U.S. The certificate in which President Benjamin Harrison appoints Harris as Virginia's representative at the World's Columbian Exposition of 1892 is located in the oversize miscellaneous file. His handwritten autobiography,(photocopy) dated 1898, gives many particulars of his life. For a transcription of the autobiography see, <title render="doublequote">Of Men and Measures: The Memoirs of John T. Harris of Virginia</title> by Dale F. Harter, 1999.
</p>
</scopecontent>
